A Marsh, with lilies on the edge—  
How solemn is a thousand graves—  
And waters softly—drift away  
Outside the house—a White row  

To keep a friendly lip,  
The Sheep, with green to hold  
When all we're passed without remorse  
True tides of joy behold—  


- Emily Dickinson
